hom.sense:
A thing, an affair, or a business, of magnitude. (IAạr, Th, Ḳ.) It is related in a trad. that Moḥammad promised a certain man to go forth to him, and delayed to do so; and when he went forth, he said to him, XagalaniI xaTomN, meaning A thing,, &c., of magnitude [occupied me so as to divert me]; 


as though the m were a substitute for b: (IAạr, Th, TA:) but IAth says that it may mean † a thing,, &c., that withheld me, or prevented me, 
[see 1,] 
from going forth. (TA.)

entry.sense:
